Franz Nahrada:

"Reponsible Territories are a new concept initiated by IRIS.
These are towns and/or regions where different methods of fighting poverty
and social exclusion are working together : conventional humanitarian aid
methods (those of public authorities and NGOs) and alternative methods of
the responsible economy.

In Responsible Territories, public authorities, enterprises, associations
and citizens are responsible together for the well being of all and the
social integration of vulnerable populations.
In Responsible Territories, responsible economy is well developed and is
working together with conventionnal humanitarian aid methods in order to
create a sustainable humanity."

